PRISONER OF WAR EXPERIENCES IN WORLD WAR II 
Creviston, U.S. Army tank commander, recalls his experiences during WWII: enlistment and training; landing on Utah Beach in Normandy; capture by the Germans; forced march and beatings; liberation; and the lasting effects of being a POW.1 tape, 90 mins., 20 pp.
Interview by Glenn Kniss, 1985 
